This paper deals with the analysis of training over-parameterized neural networks, which is a central topic in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the mean-field analysis of two-layer neural networks and provides non-asymptotic rates and generalization bounds. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, the paper also deals with optimization algorithms and information theory, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior of neural networks in a generalized neural tangent kernel regime, which is related to the study of neural network architectures and their properties, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper provides insights into the connection between mean-field analysis and neural tangent kernel-based analysis, which is related to the theoretical foundations of deep learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
